I'm stuck on a failing CI/CD pipeline. I implemented a plugin system where the trait is called Plugin and I store pointers to implementations in a HashMap keyed by name strings. The code looks like this: let mut registry = std::collections::HashMap::new();
let p1 = Box::new(MyPlugin {});
registry.insert(p1.name().to_string(), p1 as &dyn Plugin);

I thought I could just cast to the trait object with p1 as &dyn Plugin, but now it's failing because the trait is not Send + Sync. The docs say dynamic dispatch requires the trait bounds on the impl block to be the same for all implementations in the registry. My first implementation has #[derive(Debug)] while my second one doesn't. I thought deriving traits like Debug or Clone would just add a bound, but maybe it's more than that?
